No matter how good the scoring system works, if people are not using it, it is not helpful. Due to its ethical dilemma in determining „the truth“, it can also never really be made „mandatory“. I might think that the question „How can the usage barrier be lowered, to make sure more people use it?“ is more difficult than the tool itself.
